<topic id="convert-JSON-to-XML">
  <title>JSON to XML Converter</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>JSON documents<indexterm>JSON to XML converter</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Convert JSON to XML</indexterm>
        <indexterm>JSON to XML tool</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> includes a useful and simple tool for converting JSON files to XML. It
      can be found in the <uicontrol product="developer editor">Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol
        product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML Tools</uicontrol> menu.</p>
    <p>To convert a JSON document to XML, follow these steps:</p>
    <ol id="procedure-import-from-HTML">
      <li>
        <ph>Select the <uicontrol>JSON to XML</uicontrol> action from the <uicontrol
            product="developer editor">Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML Tools</uicontrol> menu.</ph>
        <itemgroup><ph>The <uicontrol>JSON to XML</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed:</ph><p>
            <fig>
              <title>JSON to XML Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/convert-json-to-xml-dialog.png" id="image_twc_5qf_jd"/>
            </fig>
          </p></itemgroup>
      </li>
      <li>
        <ph>Choose or enter the <uicontrol>Input URL</uicontrol> of the JSON document.</ph>
      </li>
      <li>
        <ph>Choose the path of the <uicontrol>Output file</uicontrol> that will contain the
          resulting XML document.</ph>
      </li>
      <li>
        <ph>Select the <uicontrol>Open in Editor</uicontrol> option to open the resulting XML
          document in the main editing pane.</ph>
      </li>
      <li>
        <ph>Click the <uicontrol>Convert</uicontrol> button.</ph>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p>The original JSON document is now converted to an XML document.</p>
    <p>
      <fig>
        <title>Example: XML to JSON Operation Result</title>
        <image href="../img/convert-json-to-xml.png" id="image_pgg_nkf_jd"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
  </body>
</topic>
